
---


@startuml

' Classes
class WebPortal {
  - version: String
  - url: String
}

class Building {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - energyClass: String (A, B, C, D)
  - address: String
  - yearOfConstruction: Integer
  - owner: User
  - additionalEntries: List<Entry>
  - images: List<Image>
  - profilePhoto: Image
}

class User {
  - username: String
  - email: String
  - password: String
  - activated: Boolean
}

class Entry {
  - name: String
  - isPublic: Boolean
  + getType(): String
}

class TextEntry <|-- Entry {
  - content: String
}

class NumericEntry <|-- Entry {
  - value: Float
  - unit: String
}

class Image {
  - filename: String
}

class Administrator <|-- User {
  - idCardNumber: String
}

class Comment {
  - content: String
  - author: User
  - building: Building
}

' Relationships
WebPortal "1" --> "*" Building
Building "1" --> "*" Entry
Building "1" --> "*" Image
User "1" --> "*" Building
User "1" --> "*" Comment
Administrator "1" --> "*" User

' Use Cases
actor Visitor
actor User
actor Administrator

usecase "Register" as UC1
usecase "Activate Account" as UC2
usecase "Login" as UC3
usecase "Create Building" as UC4
usecase "Manage Building Entries" as UC5
usecase "Add Additional Entry" as UC6
usecase "Comment on Building" as UC7
usecase "Search Buildings" as UC8
usecase "Delete Comment" as UC9
usecase "Setup User" as UC10

Visitor --> UC1 : Register
Visitor --> UC8 : Search Buildings
UC1 --> UC2 : Email confirmation
UC2 --> UC3 : Automatically login after activation
User --> UC3 : Login
User --> UC4 : Create Building
User --> UC5 : Manage Building Entries
User --> UC6 : Add Additional Entry
User --> UC7 : Comment on Building
Administrator --> UC10 : Setup User
Administrator --> UC9 : Delete Comment

' Generalization
User <|-- Administrator

@enduml

---

### ✅ **Explanation of Key Elements**

- **Classes & Attributes**:
  - `Building` contains all the core data like ID, name, energy class, etc.
  - `Entry` is an abstract class with two concrete subclasses: `TextEntry` and `NumericEntry`.
  - `User` is extended by `Administrator` with an extra attribute (`idCardNumber`).
  - `Image` is used for storing file names; one image per building is marked as the profile photo.

- **Use Cases**:
  - **UC1 (Register)**: Visitors register with a username, email, and password.
  - **UC2 (Activate Account)**: System sends a confirmation link; upon clicking, the user becomes active.
  - **UC3 (Login)**: Only activated users can log in.
  - **UC4 (Create Building)**: Users create new buildings and assign them to themselves.
  - **UC5 (Manage Building Entries)**: Owners can edit/delete entries they added.
  - **UC6 (Add Additional Entry)**: Users add either text or numeric data to their buildings.
  - **UC7 (Comment on Building)**: Any logged-in user can comment on other users’ buildings.
  - **UC8 (Search Buildings)**: All visitors can perform full-text searches.
  - **UC9 (Delete Comment)**: Administrators delete inappropriate comments.
  - **UC10 (Setup User)**: Admins manually activate registered users before they receive an activation email.

- **Generalization**:
  - `Administrator` inherits from `User`.

